{\an8}Great job, Dark Secret.

1417
00:33:11,180 --> 00:33:12,700
C'est à votre tour de nous aider.

1418
00:33:11,180 --> 00:33:12,700
{\an8}Now it's your turn to help us.

1419
00:33:13,140 --> 00:33:15,640
Ma Banana-Outils a les moyens de nous faire sortir d'ici

1420
00:33:13,140 --> 00:33:15,640
{\an8}My pouch has just the thing to get us out of here.

1421
00:33:15,880 --> 00:33:16,840
Tout le monde avec moi

1422
00:33:15,880 --> 00:33:16,840
{\an8}Everybody say, "Oh, Pouchy!"

1423
00:33:17,500 --> 00:33:19,160
Oh Banana-Outils

1424
00:33:20,520 --> 00:33:22,220
Oh Banana-Outils

1425
00:33:20,520 --> 00:33:22,220
{\an8}Oh, Pouchy!

1426
00:33:25,000 --> 00:33:27,440
Salut les amis, je suis Banana-Outils

1427
00:33:25,000 --> 00:33:27,440
{\an8}Hi, everybody. I'm Pouchy.

1428
00:33:27,700 --> 00:33:29,040
Banana, il faut qu'on s'échappe

1429
00:33:27,700 --> 00:33:29,040
{\an8}Pouchy, we need to escape.

1430
00:33:29,250 --> 00:33:31,120
As-tu quelque chose qui pourrait nous sauver?

1431
00:33:29,250 --> 00:33:31,120
{\an8}Do you have anything that can help us?

1432
00:33:31,240 --> 00:33:32,740
Je contiens toutes sortes d'objets

1433
00:33:31,240 --> 00:33:32,740
{\an8}I have lots of items.

1434
00:33:32,880 --> 00:33:34,900
A votre avis, lequel conviendra le mieux?

1435
00:33:32,880 --> 00:33:34,900
{\an8}Which one do you think will work the best?

1436
00:33:35,300 --> 00:33:36,100
Une tomate?

1437
00:33:35,300 --> 00:33:36,100
{\an8}A tomato...

1438
00:33:36,690 --> 00:33:37,460
Une grenouille?

1439
00:33:36,690 --> 00:33:37,460
{\an8}a frog...

1440
00:33:38,100 --> 00:33:40,240
Ou un bâton de dynamite?

1441
00:33:38,100 --> 00:33:40,240
{\an8}or exploding dynamite?

1442
00:33:40,260 --> 00:33:41,600
Ok, c'est bon, tu peux partir

1443
00:33:40,260 --> 00:33:41,600
{\an8}Oh, for crying out loud.

1444
00:33:43,820 --> 00:33:46,000
Oui, on a réussi, les amis

1445
00:33:43,820 --> 00:33:46,000
{\an8}Yay! We did it, everyone!

1446
00:33:46,240 --> 00:33:48,440
Chantons tous la chanson du triomphe

1447
00:33:46,240 --> 00:33:48,440
{\an8}Let's all sing the "We did it" song.

1448
00:33:48,980 --> 00:33:49,420
Rêta!

1449
00:33:48,980 --> 00:33:49,420
{\an8}No time!

1450
00:33:50,820 --> 00:33:51,340
Merci, mes amis

1451
00:33:50,820 --> 00:33:51,340
{\an8}Thank you, friends.

1452
00:33:51,920 --> 00:33:52,540
Je dois...

1453
00:33:53,030 --> 00:33:53,920
Je dois...

1454
00:33:53,030 --> 00:33:53,920
{\an8}I must be leaving you.

1455
00:33:53,960 --> 00:33:54,400
Vous...

1456
00:33:54,400 --> 00:33:54,620
Quittez

1457
00:33:55,460 --> 00:33:57,240
Et est-ce que Noir Secret vient avec nous?

1458
00:33:55,460 --> 00:33:57,240
{\an8}What about Dark Secret?

1459
00:33:58,820 --> 00:34:00,180
Encore trop tard

1460
00:33:58,820 --> 00:34:00,180
{\an8}Not yet.

1461
00:34:02,100 --> 00:34:03,940
Oui, ça vaut certainement mieux pour tout le monde

1462
00:34:02,100 --> 00:34:03,940
{\an8}Yeah, that's probably best for everybody.

1463
00:34:04,000 --> 00:34:05,200
Hé! Qui vous a ouvert?

1464
00:34:04,000 --> 00:34:05,200
{\an8}Hey! Who let you out? Get back in there!

1465
00:34:05,540 --> 00:34:06,160
Rentrez là-dedans!

1466
00:34:06,420 --> 00:34:07,360
Qu'est-ce que vous avez fait?

1467
00:34:06,420 --> 00:34:07,360
{\an8}- Oh, boy. - What are we gonna do?

1468
00:34:08,060 --> 00:34:09,000
Oh, m'a dégoûté

1469
00:34:08,060 --> 00:34:09,000
{\an8}Oh disgusted one...

1470
00:34:09,820 --> 00:34:11,580
Tout comme tu as eu foi en moi

1471
00:34:09,820 --> 00:34:11,580
{\an8}as you once believed in me, I will now believe in myself.

1472
00:34:11,800 --> 00:34:13,820
Désormais, j'en fois en moi également.

1473
00:34:19,240 --> 00:34:20,820
Mais enfin, qu'est-ce qu'il fait?

1474
00:34:19,240 --> 00:34:20,820
{\an8}Wait. What?

1475
00:34:29,340 --> 00:34:31,240
Oh, qu'est-ce qu'il se passe? Qu'est-ce que...

1476
00:34:29,996 --> 00:34:31,706
{\an8}What's happening?

1477
00:34:36,002 --> 00:34:37,003
{\an8}No...

1478
00:34:37,080 --> 00:34:39,020
-Kiff, au secours! -Attendez-vous!

1479
00:34:37,080 --> 00:34:39,020
{\an8}Dave, help! Help!

1480
00:34:38,338 --> 00:34:39,339
{\an8}Hold on!

1481
00:34:39,839 --> 00:34:40,840
{\an8}Dave!

1482
00:34:42,800 --> 00:34:44,052
{\an8}Lance!

1483
00:34:44,219 --> 00:34:45,220
{\an8}Goodbye, friends.

1484
00:34:45,387 --> 00:34:47,014
{\an8}Hello, destiny!

1485
00:34:47,179 --> 00:34:48,899
Y'a plus qu'à espérer qu'il trouve sa voie

1486
00:34:47,764 --> 00:34:49,099
{\an8}Well, there's a lid for every pot.

1487
00:34:49,399 --> 00:34:49,620
Venez

1488
00:34:49,399 --> 00:34:49,620
{\an8}Come on!

1489
00:34:52,099 --> 00:34:53,620
Qu'est-ce qu'on va faire? Qu'est-ce qu'on va faire?

1490
00:34:52,099 --> 00:34:53,620
{\an8}What do we do? What do we do?

1491
00:34:53,720 --> 00:34:55,360
Oh, collègue, arrête! Où est-ce que tu vas?

1492
00:34:53,720 --> 00:34:55,360
{\an8}Whoa, Anger, stop. Where are you going?

1493
00:34:55,480 --> 00:34:57,980
Je retourne au quartier cérébral pour aider Riley

1494
00:34:55,480 --> 00:34:57,980
{\an8}Back to Headquarters... to help Riley!

1495
00:34:58,320 --> 00:35:01,200
Mais Riley n'est pas là-haut, elle est là-bas, d'accord?

1496
00:34:58,320 --> 00:35:01,200
{\an8}Riley's not up there.

1497
00:34:59,859 --> 00:35:01,319
{\an8}She's out there.

1498
00:35:01,620 --> 00:35:04,100
Et on ne peut rien pour elle sans son estime de soi

1499
00:35:01,620 --> 00:35:04,100
{\an8}We can't go back without her Sense of Self.

1500
00:35:04,360 --> 00:35:07,500
Et tu es en train de suggérer qu'on aille se perdre dans les tréfonds de la mémoire?

1501
00:35:04,360 --> 00:35:07,500
{\an8}You want us to go all the way to the Back of the Mind?

1502
00:35:08,020 --> 00:35:09,840
Non mais tu es une vie folle ma pauvre!

1503
00:35:08,020 --> 00:35:09,840
{\an8}Are you out of your mind?

1504
00:35:09,960 --> 00:35:11,180
Mais joie, comment va-t-on?

1505
00:35:09,960 --> 00:35:11,180
{\an8}But, Joy, how will we...

1506
00:35:11,200 --> 00:35:11,820
Plus de gestes!

1507
00:35:11,200 --> 00:35:11,820
{\an8}- Freeze! - Come on!

1508
00:35:12,020 --> 00:35:12,140
Venez!

1509
00:35:12,380 --> 00:35:13,160
On ne bouge plus!

1510
00:35:12,380 --> 00:35:13,160
{\an8}Hold it right there!

1511
00:35:15,060 --> 00:35:16,160
Oh, comment on va y aller?

1512
00:35:15,060 --> 00:35:16,160
{\an8}How do we get there? Do you even have a plan, Joy?

1513
00:35:16,640 --> 00:35:17,940
J'espère que tu as un plan au moins.

1514
00:35:18,120 --> 00:35:20,220
Je parie qu'Anxiété aurait un super plan.

1515
00:35:18,120 --> 00:35:20,220
{\an8}I bet Anxiety would have a really good plan...

1516
00:35:20,660 --> 00:35:22,420
Moi aussi j'ai un plan, qui n'a pas de plan.

1517
00:35:20,660 --> 00:35:22,420
{\an8}Of course I have a plan. Who doesn't have a plan?

1518
00:35:22,940 --> 00:35:24,920
Anxiété n'est pas la seule à pouvoir préparer l'avenir.

1519
00:35:22,940 --> 00:35:24,920
{\an8}Look, she's not the only one who can project the future.

1520
00:35:25,200 --> 00:35:26,840
D'abord, tout ce qu'on a à faire c'est...

1521
00:35:25,200 --> 00:35:26,840
{\an8}First, all we have to do is...

1522
00:35:28,559 --> 00:35:29,260
C'est quoi déjà?

1523
00:35:28,559 --> 00:35:29,260
{\an8}Give me a second.

1524
00:35:30,420 --> 00:35:31,940
Oui, suivre le courant de pensée.

1525
00:35:30,420 --> 00:35:31,940
{\an8}Follow the stream of consciousness...

1526
00:35:32,880 --> 00:35:35,980
Et se laisser dériver tout doucement jusqu'au tréfonds de la mémoire.

1527
00:35:32,880 --> 00:35:35,980
{\an8}and then we take a nice, easy float all the way to the Back of the Mind.

1528
00:35:36,020 --> 00:35:37,360
Nous sont enfouis tous les mains des souvenirs.

1529
00:35:36,020 --> 00:35:37,360
{\an8}- Where all the bad memories are. - Exactly.

1530
00:35:37,600 --> 00:35:40,780
Exactement! Et c'est là que nous retrouverons la Riley que nous connaissons et aimons.

1531
00:35:37,600 --> 00:35:40,780
{\an8}And there, we'll find the Riley we know and love.

1532
00:35:41,070 --> 00:35:44,500
On lui rendra son estime de soi et Riley pourra être à nouveau Riley.

1533
00:35:41,070 --> 00:35:44,500
{\an8}We'll put her Sense of Self back, and then Riley will be Riley again.

1534
00:35:44,920 --> 00:35:46,960
Bon, je te le concède. Ça pourrait bien marcher.

1535
00:35:44,920 --> 00:35:46,960
{\an8}Okay, I'm gonna give it to you. That could actually work.

1536
00:35:47,240 --> 00:35:49,340
Bien sûr que ça va marcher. Ensuite, je dirai anxiété.

1537
00:35:47,240 --> 00:35:49,340
{\an8}Yeah, it could!

1538
00:35:48,533 --> 00:35:52,579
{\an8}And then I tell Anxiety, "Hey, don't worry so much anymore."

1539
00:35:49,880 --> 00:35:52,340
Hé, arrête de t'en faire en permanence.

1540
00:35:52,590 --> 00:35:56,000
Et elle dira, wow, joie, je n'y aurais jamais pensé sans toi. Merci.

1541
00:35:52,590 --> 00:35:56,000
{\an8}And she'll say, "Wow, Joy, I never thought of that before. Thank you."

1542
00:35:56,260 --> 00:35:58,120
On se fera un gros câlin, on deviendra copine.

1543
00:35:56,260 --> 00:35:58,120
{\an8}And then we hug and become best friends...

1544
00:35:58,260 --> 00:35:59,720
Et ensuite, je la balance aux boubelles.

1545
00:35:58,260 --> 00:35:59,720
{\an8}And then I punt her into the dump.

1546
00:36:00,720 --> 00:36:01,560
Quoi? Non, collègue.

1547
00:36:00,720 --> 00:36:01,560
{\an8}What? No, Anger.

1548
00:36:01,640 --> 00:36:02,820
Ok, d'accord, pas de violence.

1549
00:36:01,640 --> 00:36:02,820
{\an8}Okay, fine. No punting.

1550
00:36:05,060 --> 00:36:07,000
Suivez-moi, je sais où est le courant de pensée.

1551
00:36:05,060 --> 00:36:07,000
{\an8}Don't worry, I know right where the stream is.

1552
00:36:07,340 --> 00:36:08,500
Tristesse et moi, on y est déjà allés.

1553
00:36:07,340 --> 00:36:08,500
{\an8}Sadness and I have been here before.

1554
00:36:08,920 --> 00:36:08,960
Oh!

1555
00:36:10,200 --> 00:36:11,580
Joie, c'est une impasse.

1556
00:36:10,200 --> 00:36:11,580
{\an8}Joy, this is a dead end.

1557
00:36:11,700 --> 00:36:14,000
Oh, ça y est! On ne sortira jamais d'ici.

1558
00:36:11,700 --> 00:36:14,000
{\an8}Those are the worst kinds of ends!

1559
00:36:14,140 --> 00:36:16,520
Mais quoi? Les choses changent aussi vite.

1560
00:36:14,140 --> 00:36:16,520
{\an8}Everything's changing so fast!

1561
00:36:17,700 --> 00:36:19,000
Bravo! On est perdus.

1562
00:36:17,700 --> 00:36:19,000
{\an8}So, we're lost.

1563
00:36:19,340 --> 00:36:21,600
Non, on n'est jamais perdus quand on s'amuse.

1564
00:36:19,340 --> 00:36:21,600
{\an8}No. You're never lost if you're having fun.

1565
00:36:21,640 --> 00:36:22,960
Il n'y a personne qui s'amuse, Joie.

1566
00:36:21,640 --> 00:36:22,960
{\an8}No one is having fun, Joy.

1567
00:36:23,160 --> 00:36:24,580
Oh, je t'en prie, regarde Tristesse.

1568
00:36:23,160 --> 00:36:24,580
{\an8}Oh, come on! Look at Sadness.

1569
00:36:24,760 --> 00:36:26,180
Elle déborde de joie.

1570
00:36:24,760 --> 00:36:26,180
{\an8}She's having a great time.

1571
00:36:27,600 --> 00:36:29,180
Je croyais que tu savais où tu allais.

1572
00:36:27,600 --> 00:36:29,180
{\an8}I thought you knew where you were going.

1573
00:36:29,320 --> 00:36:31,360
Je le savais, je le sais. Laisse-moi juste un moment.

1574
00:36:29,320 --> 00:36:31,360
{\an8}I do. I did.

1575
00:36:30,658 --> 00:36:32,119
{\an8}- I just need a moment. - She doesn't know.

1576
00:36:31,440 --> 00:36:32,120
Elle n'en dit rien du tout.

1577
00:36:32,180 --> 00:36:33,380
On ne sortira jamais d'ici.

1578
00:36:32,180 --> 00:36:33,380
{\an8}We're stuck here!

1579
00:36:34,800 --> 00:36:36,240
Oh, il est réveillé.

1580
00:36:34,800 --> 00:36:36,240
{\an8}Riley's awake.

1581
00:36:36,360 --> 00:36:38,740
Quoi? Il est bien trop tôt. Qu'est-ce qu'ils sont en train de lui faire?

1582
00:36:36,360 --> 00:36:38,740
{\an8}Wait, she's up too early. What are they doing to her?

1583
00:36:39,180 --> 00:36:40,420
Venez, on va prendre un autre chemin.

1584
00:36:39,180 --> 00:36:40,420
{\an8}Come on, we'll find another way.

1585
00:36:42,320 --> 00:36:43,840
Ne t'en fais pas, Riley. On arrive.

1586
00:36:42,320 --> 00:36:43,840
{\an8}Don't worry, Riley. We're coming.

1587
00:36:51,900 --> 00:36:53,700
Pourquoi est-ce qu'on s'est levé si tôt?

1588
00:36:51,900 --> 00:36:53,700
{\an8}Why are we up so early?

1589
00:36:53,760 --> 00:36:56,000
Parce qu'il est temps de passer à la vitesse supérieure.

1590
00:36:53,760 --> 00:36:56,000
{\an8}Because, mon ami, we need to speed things up...

1591
00:36:56,340 --> 00:36:59,540
Alors on va chausser nos pattes en beaucoup plus tôt et s'entraîner comme jamais.

1592
00:36:56,340 --> 00:36:59,540
{\an8}and that means we hit the ice early...

1593
00:36:57,769 --> 00:37:00,397
{\an8}and practice like we've never practiced before.

1594
00:37:00,080 --> 00:37:02,020
Je croyais qu'on était super doués.

1595
00:37:00,080 --> 00:37:02,020
{\an8}Aren't we already good at hockey?

1596
00:37:02,360 --> 00:37:05,100
On l'est! Mais les feuilles rottes se sont encore plus fortes.

1597
00:37:02,360 --> 00:37:05,100
{\an8}We're good.

1598
00:37:03,275 --> 00:37:04,817
{\an8}But the Fire Hawks are great.

1599
00:37:05,140 --> 00:37:05,640
Exactement.

1600
00:37:05,140 --> 00:37:05,640
{\an8}That's right!

1601
00:37:09,520 --> 00:37:11,920
A chaque fois qu'on rate au but, on doit faire le tour de la patinoire

1602
00:37:09,520 --> 00:37:11,920
{\an8}Every time we miss, we skate a lap around the rink.

1603
00:37:12,240 --> 00:37:13,780
Le hockey, c'est pas un jeu, mais un sport

1604
00:37:12,240 --> 00:37:13,780
{\an8}Hockey is not a game, it is a sport.

1605
00:37:25,505 --> 00:37:26,839
{\an8}- Yes! - Wow.

1606
00:37:26,740 --> 00:37:28,600
Wow, c'était vraiment impressionnant

1607
00:37:26,740 --> 00:37:28,600
{\an8}That was amazing.

1608
00:37:28,660 --> 00:37:30,960
On doit être aussi bonne à chaque fois, on n'a pas le droit à l'erreur

1609
00:37:28,660 --> 00:37:30,960
{\an8}We need to be that good every time. Let's run it again.

1610
00:37:31,140 --> 00:37:31,700
On recommence

1611
00:37:32,080 --> 00:37:34,059
Je vois que je ne suis pas la seule qui aime s'entraîner de bonheur

1612
00:37:32,080 --> 00:37:34,059
{\an8}Hey, I see I'm not the only one who likes to start early.

1613
00:37:34,080 --> 00:37:36,200
Je ne crois pas, c'est Val! On a eu la même idée!

1614
00:37:34,080 --> 00:37:36,200
{\an8}You guys, it's Val!

1615
00:37:35,140 --> 00:37:36,308
{\an8}We had the same idea.

1616
00:37:36,360 --> 00:37:37,740
On se ressemble trop, on est pareil!

1617
00:37:36,360 --> 00:37:37,740
{\an8}We're basically the same person. We're gonna be best friends.

1618
00:37:38,300 --> 00:37:39,360
Ça va être notre meilleur ami!

1619
00:37:39,460 --> 00:37:40,280
Ça fait longtemps que t'es là?

1620
00:37:39,460 --> 00:37:40,280
{\an8}How long have you been here?

1621
00:37:40,920 --> 00:37:42,600
Je... je sais pas trop... peut-être une heure?

1622
00:37:40,920 --> 00:37:42,600
{\an8}I don't know. Maybe an hour.

1623
00:37:43,020 --> 00:37:44,920
J'avais juste besoin de m'entraîner un peu plus.

1624
00:37:43,020 --> 00:37:44,920
{\an8}I just wanted to get in some extra ice time.

1625
00:37:45,320 --> 00:37:46,480
Je te comprends, je suis comme toi.

1626
00:37:45,320 --> 00:37:46,480
{\an8}I'm the same way.

1627
00:37:46,620 --> 00:37:48,120
Vous avez entendu? Elle nous comprend.

1628
00:37:46,620 --> 00:37:48,120
{\an8}Oh, my gosh. She gets us.

1629
00:37:48,320 --> 00:37:50,600
Tu vois, j'ai bien fait de dire aux filles de croire en toi.

1630
00:37:48,320 --> 00:37:50,600
{\an8}See? I told the other girls you'd figure it out.

1631
00:37:50,880 --> 00:37:52,200
T'as ce qu'il faut pour être la meilleure.

1632
00:37:50,880 --> 00:37:52,200
{\an8}You get what it takes to be the best.

1633
00:37:55,080 --> 00:37:57,780
Ça y est, on est copines, j'en reviens pas! C'est génial!

1634
00:37:55,080 --> 00:37:57,780
{\an8}Look at us.

1635
00:37:56,203 --> 00:37:57,870
{\an8}This is going great!

1636
00:37:58,020 --> 00:38:00,520
Ouais, mais il faut que Val devienne notre meilleure copine.

1637
00:37:58,020 --> 00:38:00,520
{\an8}Yeah! But we need Val to really like us.

1638
00:38:00,700 --> 00:38:02,560
Oh, alors on devrait lui poser plein de questions!

1639
00:38:00,700 --> 00:38:02,560
{\an8}We should ask Val lots of questions.

1640
00:38:03,060 --> 00:38:04,860
Les gens adorent qu'on s'intéresse à eux!

1641
00:38:03,060 --> 00:38:04,860
{\an8}People love talking about themselves.

1642
00:38:04,920 --> 00:38:07,860
Et pour toi, ça s'est passé comment, ton année recrue dans les Firehawks?

